README.md
     1вҶ’log
     4вҶ’A Rust library providing a lightweight logging *facade*.
     5вҶ’
     6вҶ’[![Build status](https://img.shields.io/github/actions/workflow/status/rust-lang/log/main.yml?branch=master)](https://github.com/rust-lang/log/actions)
     7вҶ’[![Latest version](https://img.shields.io/crates/v/log.svg)](https://crates.io/crates/log)
     8вҶ’[![Documentation](https://docs.rs/log/badge.svg)](https://docs.rs/log)
     9вҶ’![License](https://img.shields.io/crates/l/log.svg)
    10вҶ’
    11вҶ’* [`log` documentation](https://docs.rs/log)
      вҶ’вҖҰ
    19вҶ’## Minimum supported `rustc`
    21вҶ’`1.68.0+`
    22вҶ’
    23вҶ’This version is explicitly tested in CI and may be bumped in any release as needed. Maintaining compatibility with older compilers is a priority though, so the bar for bumping the minimum supported version is set very high. Any changes to the supported minimum version will be called out in the release notes.
    24вҶ’
    25вҶ’## Usage
    27вҶ’### In libraries
    29вҶ’Libraries should link only to the `log` crate, and use the provided macros to
    30вҶ’log whatever information will be useful to downstream consumers:
    31вҶ’
    32вҶ’```toml
    33вҶ’[dependencies]
    34вҶ’log = "0.4"
    35вҶ’```
    36вҶ’
    37вҶ’```rust
    38вҶ’use log::{info, trace, warn};
    39вҶ’
    40вҶ’pub fn shave_the_yak(yak: &mut Yak) {
    41вҶ’    trace!("Commencing yak shaving");
    42вҶ’
    43вҶ’    loop {
    44вҶ’        match find_a_razor() {
    45вҶ’            Ok(razor) => {
    46вҶ’                info!("Razor located: {razor}");
    47вҶ’                yak.shave(razor);
    48вҶ’                break;
    49вҶ’            }
    50вҶ’            Err(err) => {
    51вҶ’                warn!("Unable to locate a razor: {err}, retrying");
    52вҶ’            }
    53вҶ’        }
    54вҶ’    }
    55вҶ’}
    56вҶ’```
    57вҶ’
    58вҶ’### In executables
    60вҶ’In order to produce log output, executables have to use a logger implementation compatible with the facade.
    61вҶ’There are many available implementations to choose from, here are some options:
    62вҶ’
    63вҶ’* Simple minimal loggers:
    64вҶ’    * [`env_logger`](https://docs.rs/env_logger/*/env_logger/)
    65вҶ’    * [`colog`](https://docs.rs/colog/*/colog/)
    66вҶ’    * [`simple_logger`](https://docs.rs/simple_logger/*/simple_logger/)
    67вҶ’    * [`simplelog`](https://docs.rs/simplelog/*/simplelog/)
    68вҶ’    * [`pretty_env_logger`](https://docs.rs/pretty_env_logger/*/pretty_env_logger/)
    69вҶ’    * [`stderrlog`](https://docs.rs/stderrlog/*/stderrlog/)
    70вҶ’    * [`flexi_logger`](https://docs.rs/flexi_logger/*/flexi_logger/)
    71вҶ’    * [`call_logger`](https://docs.rs/call_logger/*/call_logger/)
    72вҶ’    * [`std-logger`](https://docs.rs/std-logger/*/std_logger/)
    73вҶ’    * [`structured-logger`](https://docs.rs/structured-logger/latest/structured_logger/)
    74вҶ’    * [`clang_log`](https://docs.rs/clang_log/latest/clang_log)
    75вҶ’    * [`ftail`](https://docs.rs/ftail/latest/ftail/)
    76вҶ’* Complex configurable frameworks:
    77вҶ’    * [`log4rs`](https://docs.rs/log4rs/*/log4rs/)
    78вҶ’    * [`logforth`](https://docs.rs/logforth/*/logforth/)
    79вҶ’    * [`fern`](https://docs.rs/fern/*/fern/)
      вҶ’вҖҰ
